Document: GLTFPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: Represents a physics body within a GLTF scene.

Inherits: Node3D < Node < Object

GLTFPhysicsBody is a Node3D that represents a physics body within a GLTF scene. It is used to import physics properties from GLTF files, such as rigid bodies, static bodies, and kinematic bodies. This node allows you to define and configure physics interactions for your 3D models directly within the Godot editor, leveraging the imported GLTF data.
---CHUNK---
Document: GLTFPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: Represents a glTF physics body.
---CHUNK---
Document: GLTFPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: Describes the GLTFPhysicsBody class, which acts as an intermediary for OMI_physics_body glTF data.

GLTFPhysicsBody
Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

Description
Represents a physics body as an intermediary between the OMI_physics_body glTF data and Godot's nodes, and it's abstracted in a way that allows adding support for different glTF physics extensions in the future.
---CHUNK---
Document: GltfPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: This document describes the GltfPhysicsBody class, which is part of the glTF physics body extension for Godot.

This class is part of the glTF physics body extension for Godot. It allows for the definition of physics properties for glTF nodes.

Inherits: Object

Properties:
- body_type (int): The type of physics body. Possible values are: 0 (Static), 1 (Kinematic), 2 (Rigid). Default: 0.
- mass (float): The mass of the physics body. Default: 1.0.
- friction (float): The friction of the physics body. Default: 0.5.
- bounce (float): The bounciness of the physics body. Default: 0.0.
- linear_damping (float): The linear damping of the physics body. Default: 0.1.
- angular_damping (float): The angular damping of the physics body. Default: 0.1.
- gravity_scale (float): The scale of gravity applied to the physics body. Default: 1.0.
- continuous_cd (bool): Whether to use continuous collision detection. Default: false.
- lock_rotation_x (bool): Whether to lock rotation on the X axis. Default: false.
- lock_rotation_y (bool): Whether to lock rotation on the Y axis. Default: false.
- lock_rotation_z (bool): Whether to lock rotation on the Z axis. Default: false.
- linear_velocity (Vector3): The linear velocity of the physics body.
- angular_velocity (Vector3): The angular velocity of the physics body.
- can_sleep (bool): Whether the physics body can sleep. Default: true.
- max_contacts_reported (int): The maximum number of contacts to report. Default: 0.
- collision_layer (int): The collision layer the body belongs to. Default: 1.
- collision_mask (int): The collision mask for the body. Default: 1.
- disable_mode (int): The disable mode for the body. Possible values are: 0 (Inherit), 1 (Active), 2 (Passive), 3 (Remove). Default: 0.
- scene_file_path (String): The path to the scene file for the physics body.
- scene_packed (PackedScene): The packed scene for the physics body.
- scene_instancing_script (String): The script used for instancing the scene.
- scene_instancing_script_source (String): The source code of the script used for instancing the scene.

