Document: GLTFPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for a physics body within a GLTF scene.

Properties
* angular_velocity (Vector3): The angular velocity of the physics body. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
* body_type (String): The type of physics body. Default: "rigid".
* center_of_mass (Vector3): The center of mass for the physics body. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
* inertia_diagonal (Vector3): The diagonal components of the inertia tensor. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
* inertia_orientation (Quaternion): The orientation of the inertia tensor. Default: Quaternion(0, 0, 0, 1).
* inertia_tensor (Basis): The inertia tensor of the physics body. Default: Basis(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
* linear_velocity (Vector3): The linear velocity of the physics body. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
* mass (float): The mass of the physics body. Default: 1.0.
---CHUNK---
Document: GLTFPhysicsBody
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfphysicsbody.rst
Summary: Defines methods for converting GLTF physics bodies to and from dictionary and node representations.

Method: from_dictionary(dictionary: Dictionary) → GLTFPhysicsBody
static
Creates a GLTFPhysicsBody from a dictionary representation.

Method: from_node(body_node: CollisionObject3D) → GLTFPhysicsBody
static
Creates a GLTFPhysicsBody from a CollisionObject3D node.

Method: to_dictionary() → Dictionary
const
Converts the GLTFPhysicsBody to a dictionary representation.

Method: to_node() → CollisionObject3D
const
Converts the GLTFPhysicsBody to a CollisionObject3D node.
